at the constructor use:
`new LurchTable<TKey, TValue>(LurchTableOrder.Access, capacity, EqualityComparer<TKey>.Default)
`
the lucene get method expect for default(TValue) or null, but the LurchTable throw exception,
so just wrap the get method with:
`TValue result;
if (!lru.TryGetValue(key, out result))
{
return default(TValue);
}
return result;
`
all tests working, (include the LruHashMap), performance much faster.

